From 4bb33a007fb06969b7dc821eaf68ebfad1274863 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dirkwa <dirkwahrheit@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 22 Mar 2026 04:12:46 +1200
Subject: [PATCH] fix(admin-ui): use separate R16 share scope for legacy plugin
 bridge

Plugins built with React 16 (webpack Module Federation) crash in the
React 19 admin UI because the previous approach of temporarily hiding
R19 entries from the host share scope during container.init() left the
container holding a reference to that same scope object. When webpack
later resolved shared dependencies for chunk loading, its version
selection picked R19 (higher version, not yet marked loaded) over R16,
causing hook errors (#321) and element type mismatches.

Fix by initializing legacy containers with a dedicated R16-only share
scope so webpack's singleton resolution always picks R16. Also restore
the UMD React 16 loader with internal dispatcher linking to ensure
hooks share a single dispatcher between the plugin's CJS React 16 and
the bridged ReactDOM 16.

Keep findRemoteEntryUrl() for correct scoped package URL resolution
(e.g. _canboat_visual_analyzer to /@canboat/visual-analyzer/) and the
post-init legacy detection fallback.
